Two people were wounded in the incident but the motive for the shooting is yet to be established. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town police have confirmed that a shooting has occurred on the Okavango Bridge in Brackenfell earlier today.Two people were wounded in the incident.The motive for the shooting is still unclear.The police's Noloyiso Rxana said: &quot;I can confirm that a shooting incident occurred at 2.45pm at Okavango. Two victims were shot and wounded, a 22-year-old and an 18-year-old. A case of attempted murdered is under investigation. No one has been arrested yet.&quot;(Edited by Zunaid Ismael)